import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  import config from './utils/config'

export default ({components, ...props}) => <MDXTag name="wrapper"  components={components}>
<MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"welcome"}}>{`Welcome`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Movies Finder is an open source project allowing users to discover and look up information about a movie or TV show. The app obtains data from sources such as The Movie Databases, YouTube, and News API.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"architecture"}}>{`Architecture`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`The project relies heavily on React, a view library developed and maintained by Facebook. For stylistic purposes, Semantic UI React is used to easily produce the desired grid layout as well as to provide functionalities like modals, toggles, and autocomplete search.`}</MDXTag></MDXTag>
